    <h2>About Contact Manager</h2>
    <p><strong>Contact Manager</strong> is a simple web-based application that allows users to securely store and manage their contacts. The application is designed to be user-friendly, easy to navigate, and efficient in handling contact information. Users can sign up, log in, add new contacts, edit existing contacts, and view their contact list.</p>

    <h3>Key Features</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>User Authentication: Users can register and log in securely.</li>
        <li>Contact Management: Users can add, edit, and delete contacts.</li>
        <li>Search Functionality: Users can search for contacts by name or phone number in real-time.</li>
        <li>Responsive Design: The app is mobile-friendly and adapts to different screen sizes.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Technologies Used</h3>
    <p>The Contact Manager is built using the following technologies:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Frontend:</strong> HTML, CSS, Bootstrap, JavaScript (AJAX)</li>
        <li><strong>Backend:</strong> Node.js, Express.js</li>
        <li><strong>Database:</strong> MySQL for storing user and contact data</li>
        <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> Sessions for secure login</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>How It Works</h3>
    <p>The application stores user credentials and contact information in a MySQL database. Users can log in to access their personal contacts, and they can perform CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations on their contact list. Additionally, users can search for contacts by name or phone number using a real-time search feature that fetches results dynamically from the database without reloading the page.</p>
